    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Freeway Frustrations</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Adarsh Khalsa letter about Mar 25 article on Los Angeles art scene says Los Angeles needs better transportation for visitors (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Art's Here. Where's the Crowd?'' by Edward Wyatt [March 25]:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Art's Here. Where's the Crowd?'' by Edward Wyatt [March 25]:</p>
        <p>In reference to the lack of cultural tourists in Los Angeles, Eli Broad asks, ''Why is that?'' Two words: traffic and transportation. I live in Phoenix, and we used to travel two or three times a year to Los Angeles to view the art and shop. But we spent many hours driving between the art centers and sitting on freeways. That's why we have not been back since 2004. When that situation improves, I'll be back. Mr. Broad, what will you do about that?</p>
        <p>Adarsh Khalsa  Phoenix</p>
        <p>ART IN LOS ANGELES</p>
      </block>
